Bungoma Governor Kenneth Lusaka has nullified the recruitment of 250 reinforcement officers following a public outcry.Speaking during the funeral of Patrick Barasa in Ndegelwa, Kanduyi constituency, on Tuesday, Lusaka accused the Public Service Board of nepotism and uneven distribution of the slots.&ldquo;I have with immediate effect cancelled the entire process of recruitment of the enforcement officers. We cannot have a process where all those that have been appointed are relatives and cronies of board members,&rdquo; he said.The board recruited 250 people, instead of the 180 advertised.MCAs questioned why some wards had more recruits than others. The issue caused a heated debate.